		<group id="page-content">
			<group id="content-header" label="OVERVIEW" filteredFrom="swt">
            </group>
			<text style-id="page-title" id="page-title" filteredFrom="html">OVERVIEW</text>
			<text style-id="page-description" id="page-description">Debrief is a software application used for analysing maritime vessel tracks in 2 and 3 dimensions.  You are now looking at Debrief NG, a fresh, modular version of Debrief generated to increase the capability of maritime tactical analysts.</text>
			<text style-id="page-description" id="first-steps">If you want to get your hands dirty with Debrief open the [Tutorials] tab, and load some data.  If you want to learn more about Debrief look into one of the other tabs.</text>
			<group id="overview-links">
				<anchor id="beginAnchor"/>
				<link label="History of Debrief" url="http://org.eclipse.ui.intro/showHelpTopic?id=/org.mwc.debrief.help/html/reference/history.html&amp;embedTarget=page-content" id="history">
					<text>Where Debrief came from</text>
				</link>
				<link label="Getting data into Debrief" url="http://org.eclipse.ui.intro/showHelpTopic?id=/org.mwc.debrief.help/html/legacy/import_range_data.html&amp;embedTarget=page-content" id="data">
					<text>Find out how to get your data into Debrief</text>
				</link>
				<link label="Getting support for Debrief" url="http://org.eclipse.ui.intro/showHelpTopic?id=/org.mwc.debrief.help/html/legacy/debrief_feedback.html&amp;embedTarget=page-content" id="support">
					<text>What to do if you have any problems with Debrief</text>
				</link>
			</group>
		</group>
	</page>
