            </group>
			<text style-id="page-title" id="page-title" filteredFrom="html">TUTORIALS</text>
			<text style-id="page-description" id="page-description">Learn how to be productive using Debrief by completing tutorials that will guide you along the way.</text>
			<group id="overview-links" label="Getting started">
				<link label="Getting started with Debrief NG" url="http://org.eclipse.ui.intro/showStandby?partId=org.eclipse.platform.cheatsheet&amp;input=org.mwc.debrief.help.started.tutorial" id="cheat_started">
					<text>Configure Debrief NG and load your first data </text>
				</link>
				<link label="Single sided reconstruction with Debrief NG" url="http://org.eclipse.ui.intro/showStandby?partId=org.eclipse.platform.cheatsheet&amp;input=org.mwc.debrief.help.cheatsheet.s2r.composite" id="cheat_started">
					<text>Tidy ownship track and generate target track</text>
				</link>
			</group>
			<group id="overview-links" label="Introductory tasks">
				<text>Before you start generating and viewing plots in Debrief you have to generate a Project </text>
				<text>A Project is a place where Debrief can find your working files (and links to existing work directories).</text>
				<link label="Generating a project" url="http://org.eclipse.ui.intro/showStandby?partId=org.eclipse.platform.cheatsheet&amp;input=org.mwc.debrief.help.started.generate_project" id="generate_project">
					<text>Learn how to generate a folder to store you work (together with links to existing work)</text>
				</link>
				<link label="Getting your data into Debrief" url="http://org.eclipse.ui.intro/showStandby?partId=org.eclipse.platform.cheatsheet&amp;input=org.mwc.debrief.help.started.existing_data" id="existing_data">
					<text>Learn how to inform Debrief where your information existing plots (and data-files) are stored</text>
				</link>
				<link label="Creating a new plot" url="http://org.eclipse.ui.intro/showStandby?partId=org.eclipse.platform.cheatsheet&amp;input=org.mwc.debrief.help.started.create_plot" id="create_new_plot">
					<text>Learn how to create a blank plot, ready to import exercise data</text>
				</link>
				<link label="Opening an existing plot" url="http://org.eclipse.ui.intro/showStandby?partId=org.eclipse.platform.cheatsheet&amp;input=org.mwc.debrief.help.started.open_plot" id="open_existing_plot">
					<text>Learn how to load an existing plot into Debrief</text>
				</link>
			</group>
			<group id="overview-links" label="Solving Problems">
				<link label="Viewing the error log" url="http://org.eclipse.ui.intro/showHelpTopic?id=/org.mwc.debrief.help/html/legacy/fault_diagnosis.html" id="view_log">
